The figures of a new study commissioned by US authorities show that nearly 40% of those who have died had type 2 diabetes as an underlying disease.
When the proportion of those who had not reached the age of 65 is examined, the percentage rises to half.
The investigation of the American Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) included more than 10,000 people in 15 states who died from the coronavirus during the period from February through May.
Jonathan Wortham, an infectious disease expert at the CDC, says the results are striking, not least for those who have been diagnosed with type 2 diabetes and their loved ones.
