The virus attacks the heart, lungs, and kidneys, organs that are already weakened in many people with diabetes.
Then a high percentage of glucose and lipids in diabetics can induce a veritable "cytokine storm," as it's called when the immune system reacts too aggressively and attacks the body.
Damaged endothelial cells can also lead to inflammation, which in turn can cause a fatal blood clot.
"This is all one big jigsaw puzzle," says Dela Cruz.
Everything is interconnected.
