A new variant rather than a new species of virus
"A new virus just means that this has been an individual who came from abroad."
This is not something that has been brewing domestically," says Már Kristjánsson, chief physician at the Infectious Disease Department of the National Hospital, about the news that "a new type of virus" has been detected in the country.
